    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Buddhist rock-cut shrines or sanctuaries. a barrel-vaulted hall with stūpa as focus of worship; the term is sometimes used by itself for the hall housing the caitya (caityagṛha) or for a barrel-vaulted-window motif based on that hall-type (caitya-gavākṣa)</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
